From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Butui Hu <hot123tea123@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] COMP: Name VTK regex linker version script

GNU ld rejects combining an anonymous linker version script with another
version script that defines named version nodes. VTK's bundled libtiff uses
libtiff.map with LIBTIFF_* nodes, so Slicer's global VTK regex-hiding script
must use a named node as well.
---
 SuperBuild/vtk-hide-stdcxx-regex.ver | 12 +++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/SuperBuild/vtk-hide-stdcxx-regex.ver b/SuperBuild/vtk-hide-stdcxx-regex.ver
index 3d8e62b..f54b18f 100644
--- a/SuperBuild/vtk-hide-stdcxx-regex.ver
+++ b/SuperBuild/vtk-hide-stdcxx-regex.ver
@@ -16,8 +16,19 @@
  * Marking these libstdc++ internals "local" makes each VTK library bind its
  * own matching copy and stop participating in interposition. Every other VTK
  * symbol keeps its default (global) binding. This mirrors the symbol-control
- * approach already used by Libs/krb5-gssapi-stub/gssapi_krb5.ver.
+ * approach already used by Libs/krb5-gssapi-stub/gssapi_krb5.ver.
+ *
+ * This version node must be named. GNU ld rejects combining an anonymous
+ * version script with another script that defines named version nodes. Some
+ * VTK third-party libraries, such as bundled libtiff, add their own version
+ * scripts, so using an anonymous node here breaks those links with:
+ *
+ *   anonymous version tag cannot be combined with other version tags
+ *
+ * Do not add a global pattern here; keeping it absent preserves the default
+ * global binding for symbols not matched by the local patterns below.
  */
+SLICER_VTK_REGEX_HIDE
 {
   local:
     _ZNSt8__detail*;     /* std::__detail::  _Scanner / _Compiler / _Executor   */
-- 
2.50.0
